('Chole Bhature','1. Soak chickpeas overnight. Pressure cook with salt.\n2. Heat oil, add cumin seeds, onion paste, cook till golden.\n3. Add ginger garlic paste, tomato puree, chole masala, red chilli, salt.\n4. Add chickpeas with water, simmer 15 mins.\n5. For bhature: knead maida with yogurt, salt, baking soda. Rest 2 hours.\n6. Roll into ovals, deep fry till puffed and golden.','Indian',60,'hard',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Channa_masala.jpg/640px-Channa_masala.jpg'),
 
('Masala Dosa','1. Soak rice and urad dal separately 6 hours, grind to batter, ferment overnight.\n2. For filling: boil mash potatoes, temper mustard seeds, curry leaves, onion, turmeric.\n3. Spread thin dosa on hot tawa, add filling, fold and serve with sambar and chutney.','South Indian',30,'hard',1,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3e/Masala_dosa.jpg/640px-Masala_dosa.jpg'),
 
('Pav Bhaji','1. Boil potato, cauliflower, peas, carrot. Mash well.\n2. Heat butter, add onion, capsicum, cook till soft.\n3. Add tomato, pav bhaji masala, turmeric, red chilli, salt.\n4. Add mashed vegetables, cook 10 mins.\n5. Toast pav with butter. Serve hot.','Indian',40,'medium',2,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/31/Pav_bhaji.jpg/640px-Pav_bhaji.jpg'),
 
('Rajma Masala','1. Soak red kidney beans overnight, pressure cook.\n2. Blend onions, tomatoes, ginger garlic into paste.\n3. Cook paste, add rajma masala, garam masala.\n4. Add cooked rajma with water, simmer 20 mins.\n5. Garnish with cream and coriander.','Indian',50,'medium',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Rajma_curry.jpg/640px-Rajma_curry.jpg'),
 
('Paneer Tikka Masala','1. Marinate paneer cubes in yogurt, tikka masala, lemon juice. Grill till charred.\n2. Cook onion, tomato puree, cream with spices.\n3. Add grilled paneer, simmer 10 mins.\n4. Garnish with cream and coriander.','Indian',45,'medium',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3d/Paneer_makhani.jpg/640px-Paneer_makhani.jpg'),
 
('Aloo Gobi','1. Heat oil, add cumin seeds.\n2. Add potato cubes, fry 5 mins.\n3. Add cauliflower, turmeric, coriander powder, red chilli, salt.\n4. Cover and cook 20 mins on low flame.\n5. Add garam masala, garnish with coriander.','Indian',30,'easy',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/Aloo_gobi.jpg/640px-Aloo_gobi.jpg'),
 
('Baingan Bharta','1. Roast whole brinjal on flame till charred. Peel and mash.\n2. Cook onion, tomato, ginger garlic with spices.\n3. Add mashed brinjal, cook 10 mins.\n4. Garnish with coriander. Serve with roti.','Indian',35,'medium',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Baingan_bharta.jpg/640px-Baingan_bharta.jpg'),
 
('Malai Kofta','1. Mash paneer and boiled potato, add cornflour, roll into balls, deep fry.\n2. For gravy: blend cashews, onion, tomato.\n3. Cook paste with butter, cream, kasuri methi, garam masala.\n4. Add koftas before serving.','Indian',50,'hard',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Malai_kofta.jpg/640px-Malai_kofta.jpg'),
 
('Vegetable Biryani','1. Soak basmati rice 30 mins, parboil with whole spices.\n2. Cook vegetables with biryani masala, yogurt, mint, coriander.\n3. Layer rice and vegetables. Top with fried onions, saffron milk, ghee.\n4. Dum cook on low flame 25 mins.','Indian',70,'hard',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/Veg_Biryani.jpg/640px-Veg_Biryani.jpg'),
 
('Sambar','1. Pressure cook toor dal with tomato and turmeric.\n2. Cook tamarind extract with drumstick, brinjal, pearl onions.\n3. Add dal, sambar powder, salt, jaggery.\n4. Temper mustard seeds, curry leaves, hing in oil. Pour over sambar.','South Indian',40,'medium',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Sambar.jpg/640px-Sambar.jpg'),
 
('Medu Vada','1. Soak urad dal 4 hours, grind to thick batter.\n2. Add pepper, cumin, curry leaves, green chilli, ginger, salt.\n3. Shape into ring doughnuts, deep fry till golden and crispy.\n4. Serve with sambar and coconut chutney.','South Indian',30,'medium',4,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Medu_vada.jpg/640px-Medu_vada.jpg'),
 
('Poha','1. Rinse flattened rice and drain.\n2. Heat oil, add mustard seeds, curry leaves, green chilli, onion.\n3. Add turmeric, poha, salt, lemon juice, sugar.\n4. Garnish with coriander, sev and grated coconut.','Indian',15,'easy',1,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Poha.jpg/640px-Poha.jpg'),
 
('Upma','1. Dry roast rava till golden.\n2. Temper mustard seeds, chana dal, cashews, curry leaves, onion.\n3. Add boiling water with salt.\n4. Add rava gradually stirring continuously.\n5. Cook covered 5 mins. Add lemon juice and coriander.','South Indian',20,'easy',1,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2e/Upma.jpg/640px-Upma.jpg'),
 
('Dal Makhani','1. Soak black dal overnight, pressure cook.\n2. Cook onion, ginger garlic, tomato puree in butter.\n3. Add cooked dal, simmer 30 mins on low flame.\n4. Add cream, kasuri methi, garam masala.\n5. Serve with butter naan.','Indian',60,'medium',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Dal_makhani.jpg/640px-Dal_makhani.jpg'),
 
('Paneer Butter Masala','1. Blend tomatoes, cashews, onion into smooth paste.\n2. Cook paste in butter till deep colour.\n3. Add red chilli, coriander, kasuri methi, cream, salt.\n4. Add paneer cubes, simmer 8 mins.\n5. Serve with naan.','Indian',35,'medium',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3d/Paneer_makhani.jpg/640px-Paneer_makhani.jpg'),
 
('Gobi Manchurian','1. Make batter with maida, cornflour, soy sauce, pepper. Dip cauliflower and fry.\n2. In wok fry garlic, ginger, capsicum.\n3. Add soy sauce, chilli sauce, vinegar.\n4. Toss fried gobi. Garnish with spring onions.','Indian',40,'medium',4,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Gobi_manchurian.jpg/640px-Gobi_manchurian.jpg'),
 
('Kadai Paneer','1. Dry roast and grind coriander seeds and red chilli.\n2. Cook onion, tomatoes, ginger garlic with ground spices.\n3. Add capsicum, paneer cubes, kasuri methi, garam masala.\n4. Cook 5 mins. Serve with roti.','Indian',30,'medium',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Kadai_paneer.jpg/640px-Kadai_paneer.jpg'),
 
('Aloo Matar','1. Heat oil, add cumin, onion, ginger garlic.\n2. Add tomatoes, turmeric, red chilli, coriander powder.\n3. Add diced potatoes and peas, salt.\n4. Cover and cook 20 mins.\n5. Add garam masala and coriander.','Indian',30,'easy',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2b/Aloo_mutter.jpg/640px-Aloo_mutter.jpg'),
 
('Bhindi Masala','1. Fry okra pieces in oil till slightly crispy.\n2. Cook onion, tomato, ginger garlic with cumin, coriander, turmeric, amchur.\n3. Add fried okra, toss gently, cook 5 mins.\n4. Serve with roti.','Indian',25,'easy',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Bhindi_masala.jpg/640px-Bhindi_masala.jpg'),
 
('Matar Paneer','1. Heat oil, add cumin, bay leaf, onion paste, cook till golden.\n2. Add tomato puree, coriander, turmeric, red chilli, salt.\n3. Add green peas and paneer cubes with water.\n4. Cook 15 mins. Finish with garam masala and cream.','Indian',35,'easy',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Matar_paneer.jpg/640px-Matar_paneer.jpg'),
 
('Kichdi','1. Wash rice and moong dal.\n2. Heat ghee, add cumin, bay leaf, hing.\n3. Add rice and dal, roast 2 mins.\n4. Add turmeric, salt, water (3x ratio).\n5. Pressure cook 3 whistles. Serve with ghee and pickle.','Indian',20,'easy',2,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Dal_fry.jpg/640px-Dal_fry.jpg'),
 
('Pani Puri','1. Make stiff dough with semolina, maida, baking soda. Deep fry small circles till puffed.\n2. Blend mint, coriander, green chilli, tamarind, black salt, cumin with cold water for pani.\n3. Fill puri with mashed potato, dip in cold pani and eat immediately.','Indian',60,'hard',4,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Panipuri.jpg/640px-Panipuri.jpg'),
 
('Aloo Tikki','1. Mash boiled potatoes, add cornflour, coriander, green chilli, chaat masala.\n2. Shape into flat tikki patties.\n3. Shallow fry till golden and crispy on both sides.\n4. Serve with green chutney, tamarind chutney and sev.','Indian',30,'easy',4,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Aloo_tikki.jpg/640px-Aloo_tikki.jpg'),
 
('Dhokla','1. Mix besan, yogurt, ginger, green chilli, salt, turmeric into batter.\n2. Add eno salt, pour into greased tray and steam 15 mins.\n3. Cut into squares. Temper mustard seeds, curry leaves, sesame seeds in oil.\n4. Pour over dhokla. Garnish with coriander and coconut.','Indian',30,'medium',4,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Khaman_dhokla.jpg/640px-Khaman_dhokla.jpg'),
 
('Gulab Jamun','1. Mix khoya, maida, baking soda with milk into soft dough.\n2. Roll into smooth balls, deep fry on low flame till deep brown.\n3. Soak fried balls in warm sugar syrup with cardamom and rose water for 30 mins.','Indian',40,'medium',5,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/Gulab_jamun_%28baked_version%29.jpg/640px-Gulab_jamun_%28baked_version%29.jpg'),
 
('Chana Masala','1. Soak chickpeas overnight, pressure cook.\n2. Cook onion, tomato, ginger garlic paste in oil till deep brown.\n3. Add chana masala, cumin, coriander, turmeric, red chilli.\n4. Add chickpeas, cook 15 mins. Add amchur and garam masala.','Indian',50,'medium',3,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Channa_masala.jpg/640px-Channa_masala.jpg'),
 
('Rava Kesari','1. Roast rava in ghee till golden and fragrant.\n2. Boil water with sugar and saffron.\n3. Slowly add rava to boiling water, stirring continuously.\n4. Add cardamom, food colour, ghee. Cook till halwa consistency.\n5. Garnish with cashews and raisins.','South Indian',20,'easy',5,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/95/Rava_kesari.jpg/640px-Rava_kesari.jpg'),
 
('Lassi','1. Blend thick yogurt, cold water, sugar, cardamom till frothy.\n2. For mango lassi: add mango pulp.\n3. For salty lassi: replace sugar with salt and roasted cumin.\n4. Serve chilled with ice cubes.','Indian',5,'easy',6,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/78/Glass_of_sweet_mango_lassi.jpg/640px-Glass_of_sweet_mango_lassi.jpg'),
 
('Halwa Puri','1. Roast suji in ghee till golden. Add sugar water, cardamom, saffron. Cook to halwa.\n2. Garnish with cashews and raisins.\n3. For puri: knead wheat flour with ghee, roll circles, deep fry till puffed.','Indian',45,'medium',1,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Suji_halwa.jpg/640px-Suji_halwa.jpg'),
 
('Methi Thepla','1. Mix wheat flour, fresh methi leaves, yogurt, turmeric, red chilli, ajwain, salt.\n2. Knead into soft dough. Roll into thin rotis.\n3. Cook on tawa with oil till golden on both sides.\n4. Serve with pickle and yogurt.','Indian',30,'easy',1,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f5/Methi_thepla.jpg/640px-Methi_thepla.jpg'),
 
('Vegetable Pulao','1. Soak basmati rice 30 mins.\n2. Heat ghee, add bay leaf, cloves, cardamom, cinnamon, onion.\n3. Add ginger garlic paste, mixed vegetables.\n4. Add rice, water, salt. Cook on low flame till done.\n5. Serve with raita.','Indian',35,'easy',2,1,'approved','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Vegetable_pulao.jpg/640px-Vegetable_pulao.jpg');

